{"id": "50550", "title": "Bug 50550: PropFind 404 error after MkCol success", "description": "Bug 50550PropFind 404 error after MkCol success. This suggests that the issue may be related to caching. Note: This situation appears similar to bug 21288 (FIXED: 'DirContext caching problem with Dreamweaver 6 when recursively creating directories').

Steps to reproduce:
1. Use a jackrabbit client.
2. Create an HttpClient object: HttpClient client = new HttpClient();
3. Generate a new directory URL: String newDir = 'http://localhost:8080/webdav/output/' + UUID.randomUUID() + '/';
4. Comment out the request to make the second propfind successful: 
   - HttpMethod propFindMethod1 = new PropFindMethod(newDir);
   - client.executeMethod(propFindMethod1);
   - propFindMethod1.releaseConnection();
5. Execute a MkCol request: HttpMethod mkcolMethod = new MkColMethod(newDir);
   - client.executeMethod(mkcolMethod);
   - mkcolMethod.releaseConnection();
6. Execute a PropFind request: HttpMethod propFindMethod = new PropFindMethod(newDir);
   - client.executeMethod(propFindMethod);
   - propFindMethod.releaseConnection(); ", "OB": "A PropFind call on a resource returns a 404 error when executed after a MkCol for the same resource.", "EB": "", "SR": "The caching issue causing the 404 error needs to be fixed so that the PropFind call works correctly after the MkCol call."}

